  <span id="freeText10791928336076551137" style="display:none">I am exactly the target audience for this book, as a middle-class, whole-grain eating, own-veg-growing, food-mile worrier. And yet I hated it. There you go.<br /><br />It's the patronising tone, basically. The cultural-cringey breast beating about how awful and fat-making the US food culture is (while her family soar above it in their eccentric yet back-to-the-land way). The presentation of France and Italy in particular as fantasy places where fast food is unheard of and everyone eats three hour home made dinners every night. The passages written by her earnest teenager which...sorry, but I did not pay cash money for the musings of an earnest teenager. Also the spinach lasagna recipe. JFC, what, and also why.<br /><br />DNF at 17% before I gave in to my growing urge to go buy a Big Mac out of pure spite.</span>
