    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_156153243" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/156153243" />
    <a title="Naomi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3849903-naomi"><img alt="Naomi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499023453p2/3849903.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/156153243?book_show_action=true">Mar 23, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Naomi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Naomi" href="/user/show/3849903-naomi">Naomi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780060852566" href="/book/show/2057775.Animal_Vegetable_Miracle">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3849903-naomi?shelf=could-not-finish">could-not-finish</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer156153243" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15768932827809222561">My true GR rating: <b>0/5 stars</b><br/><br/>To call this book a trifling piece of trash is, in my opinion, giving it too much credit. This book could have been excellent given the premise of the book. Instead what we get is the author, her husband and her daughter, bloviating at how much America and Americans suck..how Europe is so much better..and the list goes on. Just your typical &quot;leftist&quot; book...She could not even look out for other research to support her &quot;claims&quot;! Instead, we are subjected to the ramblin</span>
  <span id="freeText15768932827809222561" style="display:none">My true GR rating: <b>0/5 stars</b><br /><br />To call this book a trifling piece of trash is, in my opinion, giving it too much credit. This book could have been excellent given the premise of the book. Instead what we get is the author, her husband and her daughter, bloviating at how much America and Americans suck..how Europe is so much better..and the list goes on. Just your typical "leftist" book...She could not even look out for other research to support her "claims"! Instead, we are subjected to the ramblings of her professor husband. Give me a break. In her resource section, we are then subjected to more "leftist" groups!! Unbelievable, Simply Unbelievable!!<br /><br />If I didn't have to read this book for a live book group, it would have been returned after the first 100 pages. Instead, I was forced to suffer through her holier than thou, "I am better than all of you" attitude. If authors want to understand why Americans disrespect authors so much, all they need to do is read this pile of horse manure. This is the first Barbara Kingsolver book I have read and I can guarantee, it will be my last.<br /><br />ETA: 04/17/2011~Well, Ms. Kingsolver, I would like to congratulate you. You have done what no author has ever been able to do with me before. You are the first book to ever go on a could not finish bookshelf in my 37 years of reading books. I have read numerous authors who I have not agreed with...Marx, Alinsky, both Clintons, Obama(just to name a few)..yet I have always been able to finish the book. Your book was just WAY TOO over the top though, nonsensical and propagandized. I only had 100 pages and would rather have gouges out my eyes than to finish your drivel.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15768932827809222561" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


